{"id":"2110.01260","submitter":"Haijun Liu","authors":"Haijun Liu, Minghui Dai, Xiaoqing Tian, Shan Chen, Fangfang Dong and\n  Lei Lu","title":"Modified Stoney formula for obtainment of stress within thin films on\n  large deformed isotropic circular plates","comments":null,"journal-ref":"AIP Advances 11 (2021) 125009","doi":"10.1063/5.0073795","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.app-ph","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Stoney formula is widely used to obtain the residual stress in the films on\nisotropic circular plates. However, significant errors would be introduced for\nlarge deformations because of the assumption of small deformation in the Stoney\nformula. In this study, a modified Stoney formula was proposed to extend its\nscope of application to the nonlinear domain. One-phase exponential decay\nfunction with coefficient p was used to relate the curvature of the substrate\nto the stress in the film. The coefficient p could be expressed as a function\nof the thickness, diameter, Young's modulus, and Poisson's ratio of the\ncircular plate. The linear fitting technique was applied to ascertain the\nrelationship between the coefficient p and the aforementioned parameters. The\nsimple yet accurate modified Stoney formula could be used to calculate the\nresidual stress in the film directly from the measured curvature of isotropic\ncircular plates with various dimensions and materials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Oct 2021 09:04:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-15"}
